{cmd:________________________________}

{cmd:allsynth is a user-written command made freely-available to the research community. Please cite the paper:}

{browse "https://justinwiltshire.com/s/allsynth_Wiltshire.pdf":Wiltshire, Justin C., 2022.  allsynth: (Stacked) Synthetic Control Bias-Correction Utilities for Stata. Working paper.}

{hline}

{com}. 
.         mat V = e(V_matrix)
{txt}
{com}.         esttab mat(V) using "$path/results/v-matrix/adj_mad13.dta", replace mlab(none)
{res}{txt}(output written to {browse  `"/Users/jamiepavlik/Dropbox/cuba-replication//results/v-matrix/adj_mad13.dta"'})

{com}.                          
. 
. // Adjusted Maddison Minus Transfers
. //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
. 
. allsynth adj_transf13 adj_transf13(1957) adj_transf13(1956) ///
>         adj_transf13(1953) adj_transf13(1950) adj_transf13(1947) ///
>         adj_transf13(1940)  adj_transf13(1935) $predictors, ///
>         trunit(8) trperiod($treat_y) ///
>         unitnames(country_moxlad) ///
>         resultsperiod($x_axis) ///
>         pvalues(rmspe) bcorrect(merge ridge) ///
>         keep($path/results/adj_transf13-results.dta, replace) 
{txt}{hline}
{res}Synthetic Control Method for Comparative Case Studies
